 and helped to transform the region’s geographies of race and class. While logistics provided a roadmap for capital and the state to transform Southern California, it also created pockets of resistance among labor, community, and environmental groups who argued that commodity distribution exposed them to economic and environmental precarity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aLabor movementzCaliforniazInland Empire. 0aRace discriminationzCaliforniazInland Empire. 0aRegional economicszCaliforniazInland Empire. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a2008 recession.  aeconomic crisis in america.  ahousing bubble.  ahousing crash 2008.  aimmigrants in california.  alatinx california.  arace and class in southern california.  aregional geographies of race.  aregional geography of souther california.  aresistance in southern california.  asouthern california economy.  asouthern california logistics.  asouthern california racial diversity.  asouthern california recession.  asouthern california.  asubprime crash.  aunsustainable economy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052028958140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520964181?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964181423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964181/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY